www.l7defense.com    |   info@l7defense.comThe Challenge Our Solution The OutcomesWeb Application Firewalls (WAFs) 
protect web applications by ﬁltering 
and monitoring HTTP trafﬁc. They 
typically protect web applications 
from attacks such as cross-site 
forgery, cross-site scripting (XSS), ﬁle 
inclusion, and SQL injection.
•  The on-premise data center   
 processes high volumes of   
 banking ﬁnancial transactions.
• HSystem availability was   
 impaired by low throughput   
 applicative DDoS API attacks.
•  High overheads caused by   
 updating/maintaining legacy   
 WAF defense solution.•  Full Ammune™solution suite  
 installed at the client’s data   
 center in minimal time.•  Ammune™is mitigating API attacks
 usually missed by traditional WAF   
 defenses.
• Provides extensive reporting and   
 analysis  which increases API visibility.
•  Workload of the SOC staff was    
 signiﬁcantly reduced.USE CASE  |  PROTECTING APIs IN LEGACY ENVIRONMENTS
A WAF analyzes incoming packets 
using patterns. The conﬁguration 
of WAFs can lead to false positives 
or false negatives, depending on 
their conﬁguration. They are also 
difﬁcult to conﬁgure and maintain.Percentage of Ransomware 
attacks on Small/Medium 
Businesses that still depend 
on traditional WAF security 
solutions.

maintenance and updates overloaded our SOC staff.
